We love that the Bio-Med Science Academy STEM School utilized our Wikiblock library to create an outdoor classroom space.

United Way of Portage County Ohio
May 7 at 8:47 PM Â·

UWPC COVID-19 Emergency Response Fund provided funds to The NEW Center at Northeast Ohio Medical University "One With the Community" Program and Bio-Med Science Academy STEM School.

Both programs are providing meals to the Rootstown community, Rootstown School District students who qualify for meal assistance, as well as families of BIOMED students. This program has been available twice per week. The program is administered by school admin/staff and 1000 people in Rootstown are expected to be served!

Special shoutout to the Conference Services at the NEW Center at NEOMED for prepping the food!

WAY TO GO!

Cooper Lappe, an 8th grader at Bio-Med Science Academy Middle School, worked hard over spring break to 3D print head frames for face shields to donate to frontline healthcare workers. He donated the face shields (52 total) to the Rootstown Fire Department, Summa Green ED, Western Reserve ED, an ICU nurse at Mercy Medical, and an ER doctor at Mercy Medical.

What a STRONG Sense of Community :-)

We will do our best to help everyone out but our supplies are limited

We are asking parents to sign up for a specific teacher's classroom and send a cookie of your choice for the students and teachers to enjoy. This is completely your choice of cookie, just something special they can share together. Thank you in advance for your support!

Cookies can be sent in with your student on the 16th and taken to the front desk.

We will have gluten free and nut free cookies in the office for those with allergies.

Time to show our staff how important they are to us and our children. We have decided to arrange a baked potato bar and salad lunch for the teachers on December 13th. We will have crockpots and roaster pans available to keep the potatoes hot when they are delivered in the morning. Please send all items in disposable containers as we are coming close to the Christmas break.

Please remember we do have several teachers and staff with allergy concerns: Gluten free, NUT FREE (extremely important) and ginger allergy

All items can be delivered at morning drop off with your student. Or if you chose to deliver the items yourself, please have them at the school no later than 10 a.m.

We appreciate all of your support and know this means a lot to the teachers and staff.

Here is the link to sign up for the staff appreciation lunch. We appreciate any help you are willing to give.

https://www.perfectpotluck.com/meals.php?t=BJUD8902
